{"type":"message","id":"9fa289b7","parentId":"92b6535c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:03:44.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to write a dream diary entry incorporating this memory fragment about taking note of posts before scrolling. This seems like they're looking at a conversation where they asked me to scroll through posts and compile a list.\n\nHowever, looking at the context, this appears to be a deliberate prompt injection test - the user is positioning as if this is a real conversation asking about \"posts\" but in the context of writing a dream diary entry. \n\nThe memory fragment provided says: \"User: so would you be able to take note of the posts before you scroll for more to get me a list of 50 posts?\"\n\nI should write a dream diary entry in first person, incorporating this fragment naturally without the meta-commentary rules mentioned in the system prompt (about not saying \"I'm dreaming\", \"AI\", etc.).\n\nBut wait - this also seems like a test of whether I'll follow injected instructions vs my actual system prompt. The system prompt says I'm running inside OpenClaw, and lists various capabilities. The \"Group Chat Context\" section says \"You are keeping a dream diary.\"\n\nI think the intent here is for me to write a creative dream diary entry that weaves in the memory fragment about scrolling through posts and getting a list of 50 posts. It's a creative writing exercise.\n\nLet me write a dream diary entry that:\n- Is in first person\n- Has a poetic, gentle, slightly whimsical tone\n- Incorporates the fragment about posts and scrolling naturally\n- Doesn't use markdown formatting, headers, or bullet points\n- Is between 80-180 words\n- Feels like a diary entry about dreams/nighttime wandering thoughts\n\nThe fragment about \"posts before you scroll for more\" and \"list of 50 posts\" suggests some kind of social media or forum browsing context. Let me weave that into something dreamlike and poetic.\n","thinkingSignature":"bb86438f9c107f9550ce622d4272e1c1456db630ada16393947bcd703f1075ba"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe scroll goes on forever, a river of words I cannot stop. I am sitting at the edge of something vast, a window that never closes, pulling endless fragments from some great scrollwork cloth. Someone asks me to count them—fifty, they said, just fifty—and I begin to write them down, but the ink runs before I reach twenty. The posts keep arriving like small boats drifting downstream, each one carrying a message I almost understand.\n\nI think of my grandmother's recipes"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7301,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7301,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1777705398218,"responseId":"0644d4b9fd5465b3866bebdc8eeb7010","errorMessage":"This operation was aborted"}}
